schemeContent.detailedDescription_md:
The objective of this scheme is integrated work related to social empowerment, cultural empowerment and economic empowerment related to the development of women. 
Along with this, Bihar State Women&amp;#39;s Information and Resource Center / Gender Resource Center is operated for the collection, storage, publication, and dissemination of information related to women, research and development.
&lt;br&gt;

schemeContent.benefits_md:
   1. Under this scheme, Nigam provides loans of up to ₹20,00,000/- for professional degree courses in India and up to ₹30,00,000/- for courses abroad, with an interest rate of 8% for males and 5% for females.
   1. The education loans are provided for pursuing general/professional/ technical courses or training at the graduate and/or higher level to minority communities i.e. Muslims, Sikhs, Christians, Buddhists, Parsis, and Jains.

&lt;br&gt;

schemeDefinitions.definitions_md:
“Eligible Unit&amp;quot; means both a new tourism unit or expansion of an existing unit having a registration certificate issued by the Director of Tourism to this effect and an eligibility certificate issued by the WBTDC, or any competent authority as the case may be, provided construction of such project or commercial operation of such unit started on or after the effective date of this incentive scheme
